Sketchbook nonsense.
Flavor of the day.
After much travel and a robust thanksgiving gathering it’s nice to watch the snow falling from my quiet house and goof around in my sketchbook.

If you’re in NYC this Saturday from 3-5pm I’ll be joining @richardmcguirehere and @lianafinck (both cartooning game changers) for a panel discussion that’s part of the Ted Stearn Memorial Retrospective‪ (November 29th-30th‬) at One Art Space, ‪23 Warren Street (street level) Gallery 1,TriBeCa. Ted was a truly brilliant artist. Please come see this show and celebrate his life and work.
.
.
@oneartspace #tedstearnretrospective #tedstearn #fuzzandpluck @fantagraphics

Went to Guelph (and Dominion) on my third and final day in Canada to visit with my pal Seth and see his astounding and inspiring show @agguelph
Gonna miss you, Canada!

Winnipeg Day 2. Kent Monkman exhibition and then saw Sasha Velour live at an old vaudeville theatre. The show, Smoke and Mirrors, felt like Velour’s origin story. I was blown away by the emotion and stagecraft. So proud of this amazing CCS alum.
.
.
.
.
.
#sashavelour #smokeandmirrors #kentmonkman #kentmonkmanexhibit @wag_ca #winnipegartgallery @cartoonstudies

Do I look happy? Just saw an amazing adaptation of my GN, The Golem’s Mighty Swing, and was blown away. Swipe to see more of Marcus Jamin’s amazing handiwork. Thanks to the cast and crew and everyone at the @wpgjewishtheatre for such a magical evening.
.
.
.
#3nightsinCanada, @drawnandquarterly, #golem, #baseball,  @outside_the_march

Friday night doodles

Holy cow, I'm so excited to see my Golem book adapted by Toronto puppeteer @marcus.jamin in Winnipeg (Nov. 16-24). Video preview link in bio.
.

@wpgjewishtheatre

Wrapped up our democracy tour today feeling amazed, inspired, enraged, and grateful. Love to all the wonderful teachers who invited us into their classrooms and to every last student (even the knuckleheads). Thanks so much to @cartoonstudies and @mikvachallenge for pulling this tour together, @dan_nott for his cartooning leadership on this comic, and mad respect and gratitude to Coco Fox for being an incredible presentation partner and fellow road warrior. We did it. Time to go home and sleep for a few days. #wethepeople #democracynow

All hail Lynda Barry, MacArthur award winner! She’s a transformative teacher and artist and I couldn’t be happier to see her genius recognized in this way. Go, Lynda, go!!!

Leave tomorrow for 2 weeks to visit jr. and sr. high schools in the Midwest to talk democracy and give away comics.
